# Performance Standards

## Frame Rate Targets (ADR-0014)

| Metric | Design | Ship Gate | Platform |
|--------|--------|-----------|----------|
| FPS P50 | 60 | 30 | Desktop |
| FPS P50 | 30 | 24 | Mobile |
| Frame time | < 16.6 ms | < 33.3 ms | Desktop |
| Scene load | < 3 s | < 5 s | Desktop |
| Agent first token | < 1.5 s P50 | < 2 s P95 | All |

**Design for 60, ship at 30** on reference hardware (GTX 1660 / RX 580, 1080p).

## Frontend

- Code-split scenes **per scale level**; lazy-load inactive scales.
- Apply **LOD** before high-poly meshes; frustum-cull distant entities.
- Cap `pixelRatio` at 2; reduce post-processing on mobile.
- Throttle WS-driven re-renders — batch entity diffs per frame when possible.
- Report sampled FPS to Prometheus in production (1% sample).

## Backend

- Index all foreign keys and common query filters; no N+1 (use Prisma `include` deliberately).
- Throttle WebSocket broadcasts per channel spec in `realtime.md`.
- Bull queues for simulation, training, inference — **never** block HTTP handlers on LLM calls.
- Prometheus metrics interceptor on all endpoints from day one.

## Profiling

- `@react-three/perf` in dev; manual milestone FPS checks (CI does not gate FPS).
- Track regressions in Grafana; reference `docs/canonical-numbers.md` for population limits.
- **Scene budgets** (draw calls, bundle, memory per scale): `docs/performance/performance-budget.md` — read before adding geometry or assets.
